# Proposal A: RAG-Based Financial Research Assistant

**HP + Morningstar AI Hackathon** | 4 Hours | HP ZGX Nano AI Station

---

## Overview

Build a working retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) application that answers questions about financial documents, running entirely on the ZGX Nano. By the end of the hackathon, your team will have a conversational research assistant that retrieves relevant passages from SEC filings and financial documents, generates cited and grounded answers, and runs completely locally with no cloud dependencies.

---

## What You'll Build

- A document ingestion pipeline that chunks and embeds financial research documents (analyst reports, earnings summaries, fund factsheets)
- A local vector store for semantic search over the embedded documents
- A conversational interface powered by a locally-served LLM (via Ollama) that retrieves relevant document chunks and generates cited, grounded answers
- An evaluation step comparing answer quality and latency against a baseline

---

## Technology Stack

| Layer | Tool | Notes |
|-------|------|-------|
| LLM Serving | Ollama (pre-installed via ZGX Toolkit) | Qwen3.6-35B-3A recommended; try different models if you'd like |
| Embeddings | nomic-embed-text via Ollama | Runs locally, no API keys needed |
| Vector Store | ChromaDB or FAISS | Lightweight, in-process, no external dependencies |
| Orchestration | LangChain or LlamaIndex | Good RAG abstractions, familiar to most ML teams |
| UI | Gradio or Streamlit | Both available via ZGX Toolkit, fast to scaffold |
| Experiment Tracking | MLflow (pre-installed) | Log prompt templates, retrieval metrics, latency |
| Dev Environment | VS Code + ZGX Toolkit extension | Use your own laptop; ZGX Nano handles compute |

---

## Sample Data

The ZGX Nano is pre-loaded with sample financial data in the `hackathon_data/` directory. See the data README for full details. Key resources:

- **`filings/`** - SEC 10-K full-text filings from 10 public companies (AAPL, MSFT, JPM, JNJ, XOM, PG, UNH, MA, NVDA, KO). Raw `.txt` files - chunking strategy is up to you.
- **`portfolios/`** - 5 sample equity portfolios as JSON files with holdings, weights, and sector data.
- **`compliance/`** - Restricted securities list and compliance policy rules.
- **`benchmark/`** - 10 benchmark questions with expected answers for evaluation.

